"'''Swap Meet: The Jawa's Tale'''" is a short story written by [[Kevin J. Anderson]] for ''[[Tales from the Mos Eisley Cantina]]'', which was published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[August]] [[1995]]. The story, which takes place in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], is about [[Het Nkik/Legends|Het Nkik]].

==Plot summary==
[[Het Nkik/Legends|Het Nkik]], unlike most [[Jawa/Legends|Jawas]], is not content to run away and hide when threatened. When his clan-mate and best friend [[Jek Nkik]] is [[Death/Legends|killed]] by [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] looking for [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] and [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] he buys an illegal [[DL-44 heavy blaster pistol/Legends|DL-44]] [[Blaster pistol/Legends|blaster pistol]] at a Jawa annual swap-meet, sets off to [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] for vengeance and to show other Jawas they're not powerless. He's encouraged in this by [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] when they meet at the burnt-out wreckage of Jek's [[Sandcrawler/Legends|sandcrawler]].

==Continuity==
The story incorrectly calls the [[DL-44 heavy blaster pistol/Legends|DL-44 heavy blaster pistol]] a [[Blaster rifle/Legends|blaster rifle]].

